2. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) - The paper discusses interval arithmetic-based tests and provides bounds on the complexity of the algorithm in terms of bit complexity, which is a common topic in numerical analysis. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper presents a general framework for analyzing the complexity of subdivision-based algorithms, which is a topic that falls under data structures and algorithms. 
4. cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) - The paper deals with approximating real implicit curves and surfaces, which is a common problem in symbolic computation. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the framework of continuous amortization, which is a topic that falls under systems and control.
